data.title: CONTENTdm
data.meta_description: Presumed birthplace of President Andrew Johnson in Raleigh, North Carolina. Johnson is said to have been born in this house on December 29, 1809, at its original location on Fayetteville Street.  In 1909, the Colonial Dames of America purchased the house and presented it to the City of Raleigh.  It was later relocated to the grounds of Raleigh's Mordecai Historic Park.  A duplicate of the building is located at the Andrew Johnson National Historic Site in Greeneville, Tenn.
